The Blitzboks rugby team opened their 2016-17 World Sevens Series account at the Dubai Sevens with a comfortable 46-0 win over tournament debutants Uganda on Friday.SNeil Powell s team were rampant scoring eight tries with newly crowned World Player of the Year Seabelo Senatla scoring twice and captain Philip Snyman also adding a brace.The Blitzboks moved to the top of Pool B with the victory after Scotland beat the USA 14-5 in their opening match.South Africa s Blitzboks face both the Scots and the USA later in the day.The South African Women s Sevens team were beaten 39-0 by New Zealand in the quarterfinals earlier on Friday. Blitzboks Scorers:South AfricaTries: Werner Kok Philip Snyman (2) Seabelo Senatla (2) Rosko Specman Ruhan Nel Kwagga SmithConversions: Branco du Preez (2) Justin Geduld